Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle, curving. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium, light red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie drew three such pieces (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 35; 32, 13 and 55 42) From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0392.36.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0517)
